args: It's quite dark out here, and yet you still\nsee well enough to engage in combat.\nMost impressive!
That wind really came out of nowhere.\nSome fiend up to no good, maybe?
All I know is that I can't see a darn thing\nin all this darkness! Somebody fire that\ntorch up already!
In this wind, the torch would likely blow\nout the moment we relight it.
Well, there's no way we'll get back to the\nHalidom in this darkness. What's the plan?
Allow me. I will guide the group.
As I mentioned before, I do not rely upon\nmy eyes as others do.
I am attuned to sound. So long as I can\nhear things, I can guide us.
I will lead us through the forest.
Once there, the moon can guide us home\nno matter how bad the wind may be.
Do all conductors have this skill...?
Well, I suppose we'll see how this goes.\nCome on, everyone.
The sound of the wind has changed.\nThere should be a clearing just ahead.
You figured that out just from sound?\nYou're like some kind of faerie tale hero!
You crack fiend skulls AND make music!\nIs there anything you're NOT good at?!
Ha ha! I fear you overestimate me.\nI've flaws just like anyone else.
Really? 'Cause it sure doesn't seem like it!
Where exactly did you learn your style of\nfighting, Vixel?
Oh, it's just something I picked up in\nthe rough and rowdy days after my\nvoice changed.
My memories of those times are rather...\ninteresting, so I tend not to dwell on them.
But I can tell you more if you like.
Very well. Now, we must move on,\nso please stay close, everyone.
It's all thanks to you, Vixel.
You heard every leaf fall and every tiny\nanimal footstep. That was AMAZING!
Do all you conductors have the ears of\nfruit bats or what?
This is actually an ability I've possessed\nsince I was young.
For as long as I can remember,\nevery sound has been like\nmusic to me.
Thus, even when I stopped singing, I still\nheard music ever-ringing in my ears.
Well, ain't that a hell of a thing.\nDon't it get annoying?
I suppose it has proven troublesome\non occasion.
And yet, it is precisely because I have this\nability that I was able to return to the\nworld of music.
It has proven to be a most useful talent,\nas it was today.
Ah. It seems we have guests.
What?! I don't see any fien—
He's right! Fiends! And they brought all\ntheir friends, too!
A good sound. Come, then!\nI shall conduct it for you!
You're taking two on at once, Vixel?!\nDon't be so reckless!
It will be fine. Now come, beasts!\nPlay your song for me!
Your energy is quite nice,\nbut you lack delicacy!
And so ends our song, ＂A Rhapsody\nof Three Fiends＂!
He lured the fiend to that spot and then\nlaunched a surprise attack...
Just like a true conductor—full of grace,\neven in the middle of a brawl!
Thanks to you taking out the big ones,\nwe had an easy time of it.
Well, I'm just glad you're unharmed.\nPerhaps we might take a break now?
A break? We're almost at the castle!\nI say we press on.
You may be fine, Ranzal, but there are\nthose among us who are not.
M-my apologies. After all the walking and\nfighting, I fear I'm a bit winded.
Not only do you have amazing hearing,\nbut you really look out for everyone.

An orchestra is made up of many
members, and each is essential.
My work has taught me to pay close
attention to everyone's needs.
Smart, attentive, AND thoughtful!\nYou must have to fend the ladies\noff with a stick, am I right?
Ha! Bein' coy like that is the TOTAL move\nof a ladies man! ...Hey, maybe I oughta\ntry that next time.
Oh, by all means.\nJust don't expect success.

ANYWAY, that was an impressive
display, Vixel. It's adults like you
that give the rest of us something to
aim for.
I am no adult. Nay, far from it...
